#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pre-requisites
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"confFlu" is a "common configuration package" for the OpenFOAM related
developement. For it's operation it requires "GNU automake" (tested with 1.9.6 and
1.10.2) tools to be installed in your environment.


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The installation procedure for the "confFlu" consists of the following simple steps
(it is not necessary to compile anything):

1. Start a new shell session (to ensure a clear environment).

2. Go to the source directory:

   cd <path to the sources>

3. Launch configure procidures:

   ./build_configure
   ./configure

   Make sure that after each configuration step the "--- OK ---" message is
   printed in your console.


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"confFlu" installation check
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A new file "bashrc" should appear in the source directory


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"confFlu" utility environment
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Before one starts to use "confFlu" it is necessary to source the generated "bashrc" file


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

